What to check
-------------
* Redis down
  (Redis instance is down)
* MissingBackup: time() - redis_rdb_last_save_timestamp_seconds > 60 * 60 * 24
  (Redis has not been backuped for 24 hours)
* OutOfMemory: redis_memory_used_bytes / redis_total_system_memory_bytes * 100 > 90
  (Redis is running out of memory (> 90%))
* ReplicationBroken: delta(redis_connected_slaves[1m]) < 0
  (Redis instance lost a slave)
* TooManyConnections: redis_connected_clients > 100
  (Redis instance has too many connections)
* NotEnoughConnections: redis_connected_clients < 5
  (Redis instance should have more connections (> 5))
* RejectedConnections: increase(redis_rejected_connections_total[1m]) > 0
  (Some connections to Redis has been rejected)

---


Inspiration: https://gist.github.com/luanntvn/3800a9fa007a9c49c87b6da31df1d8de

Manueller Weg (zu testen auf t74-app01):

	redis-cli
	AUTH ...
	INFO

Der AUTH-Teil kann optional sein.

Good to know: https://redis.io/commands/INFO




Ausgabe:

OK - Redis v1.2.3 on ip:port has n databases (db1, db2, dbn) with m keys. Up 3d 5h 43m. 11 connected_clients.




Daten die zu monitoren sind:
https://blog.serverdensity.com/monitor-redis/